    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem¥n¥n`nvim_exec_lua` accepts args, but `nvim_exec2()` does not. AFAIK, this means there's no ergonomic way to pass args to Vimscript (except `nvim_call_function()`?). ¥n¥nA use-case is updating buffer-local variables without a serialization roundtrip. Currently that requires building a Vimscript string:¥n¥n```lua¥nvim.api.nvim_buf_call(buf, function()¥n  vim.cmd(('let b:foo.d.a = %d'):format(a))¥n  vim.cmd(('let b:foo.d.b = %d'):format(b))¥nend)¥n```¥n¥n### Expected behavior¥n¥n- `nvim_exec2` could accept an args list similar to `nvim_exec_lua`, then callers can pass values in a readable and performant way. ¥n    - This may require introducing a `v:args` special global.¥n- `nvim_exec2` result includes a `result` field¥n    - Script can set `v:result` ?¥n¥n```lua¥nlocal r = vim.api.nvim_exec2(([[¥n  let b:foo.d.a = v:args[0]¥n  let b:foo.d.b = v:args[1]¥n]], {}, { a, b })¥n¥nvim.print(r.result)¥n```¥n¥n### Bonus¥n¥nWould this eliminate the need for:¥n¥n- `nvim_call_function` ¥n- `nvim_call_dict_function`¥n¥n### Related¥n¥n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40299",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "workaround:¥n¥n```lua¥n-- Recursive (deep) dict-merge: Vim's `extend()` is shallow :(¥nvim.cmd([[¥n  func! g:Guh__deep_extend(dst, src) abort¥n    for [l:k, l:v] in items(a:src)¥n      if type(l:v) == v:t_dict && type(get(a:dst, l:k, 0)) == v:t_dict¥n        call g:Guh__deep_extend(a:dst[l:k], l:v)¥n      else¥n        let a:dst[l:k] = l:v¥n      endif¥n    endfor¥n  endfunc¥n]])¥n¥n--- Deep-merges `dict` into `b:<b_var>`. For performance; avoids the roundtrip:¥n---¥n--- ```¥n--- local foo = vim.b.foo¥n--- foo.bar = { 窶ｦ }¥n--- vim.b.foo = foo¥n--- ```¥n---¥n--- Nested dicts merge recursively: `set_b_var(buf, 'guh', { pr_data = { n_files = N } })` updates¥n--- `b:guh.pr_data.n_files` while preserving the rest of `pr_data`). No-op if `b:<b_var>` is unset.¥n---¥n--- @param buf integer¥n--- @param b_var string Name of the buffer-local variable (e.g. ¥"foo¥" for `b:foo`).¥n--- @param dict table<string, any> Keys to (deep-)merge into `b:<b_var>`.¥nfunction M.set_b_var(buf, b_var, dict)¥n  vim.api.nvim_buf_call(buf, function()¥n    vim.b._guh_patch = dict -- Marshall one-way.¥n    vim.cmd(([[¥n      if has_key(b:, '%s') | call g:Guh__deep_extend(b:%s, b:_guh_patch) | endif¥n      unlet b:_guh_patch¥n    ]]):format(b_var, b_var))¥n  end)¥nend¥n```",
