        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I implemented this and I think it technically would eliminate the need for `nvim_call_function` and¥n`nvim_call_dict_function`, but I'm unsure whether it's worth deprecating them since it is slightly less readable/ergonomic ¥nfor the simple use case of getting the return from a single function. ¥n¥nExample:¥n¥n```lua¥n-- Regular function¥nlocal list = { 1, 'two', 3, 'four' }¥nlocal idx = 3¥n¥nlocal r1 = vim.api.nvim_call_function('get', { list, idx })¥nvim.print(r1) -- four¥n¥nlocal r2 = vim.api.nvim_exec2('let v:result = [get(v:args[0], v:args[1])]', {}, { list, idx })¥nvim.print(r2.result[1]) -- four¥n¥n-- Dict function¥nvim.api.nvim_exec2([[¥n  function! Mylen() dict¥n    return len(self.data)¥n  endfunction¥n  let mydict = {'data': [0, 1, 2, 3], 'len': function(¥"Mylen¥")}¥n]], {}, {})¥n¥nlocal d1 = vim.api.nvim_call_dict_function('mydict', 'len', {})¥nvim.print(d1) -- 4¥n¥nlocal d2 = vim.api.nvim_exec2('let v:result = [eval(v:args[0])[v:args[1]]()]', {}, { 'mydict', 'len' })¥nvim.print(d2.result[1]) -- 4¥n```¥n",
