        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for that sketch! Yeah, we can keep `nvim_call_function` and `nvim_call_dict_function`, but it may very well be a good idea to *implement them* internally as wrappers around `nvim_exec2`. ¥n¥nThen we hopefully can eliminate [`_call_function`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a1a1977c708bc9b040850cd35396a1b7657840df/src/nvim/api/vimscript.c#L200) ... which may also inform us about any rituals that are missing in `nvim_exec2`. And it aligns all of the ways to call vimscript, and ensures they all behave the same way.",
